commit.message:
Various compile fixes

    In file included from ../common/lzma/Alloc.h:7,
                     from lzma-stub.c:5:
    ../common/lzma/7zTypes.h:199: redefinition of `INT_PTR'
    ../common/lzma/7zTypes.h:133: `INT_PTR' previously declared here
    ../common/lzma/7zTypes.h:200: redefinition of `UINT_PTR'
    ../common/lzma/7zTypes.h:134: `UINT_PTR' previously declared here

    ../../common/lzma/Alloc.c: In function `SzAlignedAlloc':
    ../../common/lzma/Alloc.c:366: warning: implicit declaration of function `posix_memalign'

    In file included from ../common/lzma/LzFindMt.h:8,
                     from ../common/lzma/LzmaEnc.c:19:
    ../common/lzma/Threads.h:70:9: error: unknown type name 'cpu_set_t'
       70 | typedef cpu_set_t CCpuSet;
          |         ^~~~~~~~~

Update LZMA SDK sources to latest version

Latest version of LZMA SDK is 21.02 alpha, released on 2021-05-06.

As the latest LZMA SDK comes with native support for non-windows
targets, drop any portability fixes introduced at commits acbd342
and 613cfb4 (such as the multi-threading support for non-windows
targets from the p7zip project) as they are not longer needed here.
